data.enText: to surround a building, city, etc. with soldiers until the people inside are forced to let you in

data.chText: 巴黎被围困了四个月后被迫投降。
data.enText: Paris was besieged for four months and forced to surrender.

data.chText: 歌迷们围着售票处，试图买到音乐会门票。
data.enText: Fans besieged the box office to try and get tickets for the concert.

before.chText: 尤指令人不快或烦恼的事
before.enText: especially of sth unpleasant or annoying

data.enText: to surround sb/sth in large numbers

data.chText: 那位女演员在机场被记者团团围住。
data.enText: The actress was besieged by reporters at the airport.

data.chText: （用大量的信件、提问等）使（某人）应接不暇
data.enText: to send so many letters, ask so many questions, etc. that it is difficult for sb to deal with them all

data.chText: 广播电台疲于应付愤怒的听众打来的电话。
data.enText: The radio station was besieged with calls from angry listeners.

means: (用大量的信件、提问等)使(某人)应接不暇

tr: harass, as with questions or requests
example: The press photographers besieged the movie star

tr: surround so as to force to give up
cause to feel distressed or worried
example: She was besieged by so many problems that she got discouraged

value.def: If you are besieged by people, many people want something from you and continually bother you.

example.ex: She was besieged by the press and the public.
example.tran: 她被媒体和公众纠缠不休。

value.def: If soldiers besiege a place, they surround it and wait for the people in it to stop fighting or resisting.

example.ex: The main part of the army moved to Sevastopol to besiege the town...
example.tran: 军队主力转移到了塞瓦斯托波尔，对该城进行围攻。

example.ex: The Afghan air force was using helicopters to supply the besieged town.
example.tran: 阿富汗空军正用直升机向被围城镇提供补给。
